    - target: {fileID: 8563684494448067901, guid: 0a3b6392f04558844bd340e68ced1ff9,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Text
      value: 'In this experiment you will be asked to navigate a "Y" shaped maze
        and try to make it out. Each time you make it to the correct location you
        will hear a bell chime, however, if you enter the wrong location, you will
        hear a loud buzzer.


        You will need to successfully navigate the
        maze 6 times until you are considered done with that version. After successful
        completion of the maze, you will be introduced to another Y-maze enviroment
        where you will need to complete the same goal. There are 5 of these environments
        in total


        This experiment is purely voluntary, and you will be allowed
        to exit at any time with no consequence to yourself. The entire experiment
        should take about 30 minutes to complete.


        Controls

        W =
        Move forward

        A  = Look left

        S  = Move backwards

        D 
        = Look right'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 8857235641008765976, guid: 0a3b6392f04558844bd340e68ced1ff9,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Enabled
      value: 1
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
